{title: Behind These Prison Walls Of Love}
{artist: The Country Gentlemen}
{composer: Written by William Bolick}

[C]Behind these prison walls of [F]love dear
For[C]ever more I know I’ll [G7]be
Con[C]demned because you love [F]another
No [C]one will [G7]ever set me [C]free
[G7]In my heart sweet memories [C]linger
[D7]Of the days when you were [G7]mine
Be[C]hind these prison walls of [F]love dear
[C]Visions [G7]of a past en[C]twined
Perhaps my love for you seems [F]strange dear
[C]But it’s all I’ll ever [G7]know
So [C]I’ll content myself with [F]memories
[C]If it [G7]pleases you to [C]go
[G7]Just remember precious [C]darling
[D7]When we face the judge [G7]above
[C]All of our vows will be un[F]broken
Be[C]hind these [G7]prison walls of [C]love